{\par \b Syntax:}\par linear_regression(Lst||Mtrx(A),[Lst])\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns the coefficients a and b of y=a*x+b \par It is the best line approximation to the points where the coordinates are the rows of A (or the 2 lists).\par
{\par \b Example:}\par linear_regression([[0.0,0.0],[1.0,1.0],[2.0,4.0],[3.0,9.0],[4.0,16.0]]) returns 4.0,-2.0\par }